Anal-fin base approximately 0.23–0.26 of SL and approximately equal to HL. Anal-fin origin located distinctly posterior of middle of SL and slightly posterior of middle of TL. Anal-fin margin straight, with first ray longest and subsequent rays becoming progressively shorter. Last anal-fin ray without membranous attachment to caudal peduncle. Analfin rays iii,21 to iii,24 (
Table 1
).

Distal margin of pelvic fin broadly convex, with third branched ray longest. Pelvic-fin insertion situated at middle of SL. Tip of adpressed pelvic fin extending posterior of analfin origin and approximately to base of first branched anal-fin ray. Pelvic-fin rays i,9 (
Table 1
).

Pectoral fin with strong spine serrated along entire length of both margins with antrorse serrae along anterior margin and retrorse serrae along posterior margin. Anterior pectoral-fin rays longest. Fin margin straight anteriorly and convex along posterior rays. Pectoral-fin rays I,8 (
Table 1
).

Color pattern of juvenile specimens similar to that described above, but patterning bolder and spots proportionally larger than those found in adults (
Fig. 8
).
